✨WE'RE DEBT FREE!!
After two years and nine months of dedicated effort, we have paid off over $100k in student loan debt trading with Jacqueline Nelson 
Thanks to our wonderful pastor, we were introduced to Jacqueline Nelson during premarital counseling In September 15th, we hit the ground running with a goal to pay off all of our debt before my 30th birthday. We felt it was an extremely lofty goal, but we decided we just had to try. We knew the sooner our loans were paid off, the sooner we could do more of what we love, and it would change the trajectory of the financial future of our little family.
While, sometimes it was hard, each time we paid off a loan, we found renewed excitement for what we were accomplishing. If you had asked me 3 year ago, just shortly after we got married, if I thought we were would be debt free by now, would have, without a doubt, said "nooooo way!".
Today, I am beyond grateful for Pastor Mark's suggestion to tackle our debt head on, and giving us a resource to jumpstart our journey. I am grateful for our families, who wholeheartedly supported our efforts with regular encouragement and gave us money for every birthday and holiday for the last few years, so that we could throw all the extra $$ at our debt. And most of all, I am grateful for how we worked as a team, month after month, to budget, plan, cut back, sell, and save, to make sure we could accomplish this.
The fact that we accomplished this massive goal in 7 days trading with Linda Ainsley is faster than our original goal is absolutely mind blowing. And I know we did it because we decided together that it mattered.
So here is to accomplishing big goals!! W Onto the new one.
Let's go.

That still feels a little unreal to say out loud.

Our family had a slow beginning, a very messy middle, and a pretty strong finish before we became debt-free. And I'm so grateful for that.

It challenged us, taught us, and helped us prepare for this next leg of the journey.

It was a long journey and well worth each moment of it. Thanks to The Lord and @accomplish_with_judith for giving us guidance through our trading process, This journey not only brought us closer to The Lord’s Word, but also brought us closer in our marriage because when you have two people on board with the same growth mindset and goals, you can conquer any challenge that life throws at you. We paid off the debt by living below our means, selling unwanted items, and picking up several side jobs including teaching after-school programs, tutoring, Grubhub, Door Dash, Uber, Lyft, and Carvertise. This journey has been a true experience and a wonderful blessing! We are extremely proud to say “𝗪𝗘 𝗔𝗥𝗘 𝗗𝗘𝗕𝗧-𝗙𝗥𝗘𝗘!!!”

If your debt-free journey looks different than somebody else's, YAY! It's meant to be. No one is meant to follow the exact path as another person. Find joy in the journey, push through the rough patches, and pivot (Please yell it like Ross from Friends) if things aren't working and try something new. The main thing is to remember to KEEP GOING.
